You can use the `pos()` and `length()` functions in Perl to find the location of a regex match. Here's an example function that does what you described:

```perl
sub find_matches {
    my ($string, $regex, $global) = @_;
    my @matches;

    while ($string =~ /$regex/g) {
        my $start = pos($string) - length $&;
        my $end = pos($string) - 1;
        push @matches, [$start, $end];
        last unless $global;
    }

    return @matches;
}
```

